result.execSummary:
The defendant Jennifer Lynn Bender was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Reckless Driving-Endanger Safety. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

15CM259, 15CM260 & 16CM4 Cases called @ 2:Defendant Jennifer Lynn Bender in court with attorney Jeremy J Guza.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 15CM259 - Amended complaint stated. Receipt admitted - reading waived.  Defendant advised of potential punishment.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  15CM260 - Upon motion of the State the Court amends Ct 1 to Reckless Driving contrary to Wis Stat 346.62(2). Plea: 15CM259: Ct 1-Guilty. 15CM260: Ct 1-Guilty. 16CM4: Ct 1-Guilty.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. 15CM259: Ct 2 - DRI. 15CM260: Ct 2 - DRI. 16CM4: Ct 2 - DRI. 15TR1708 & 15TR1709 - DRI. Sentencing argument by Atty Guza. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Statement by DE. Court orders: 

15CM259: 45 days WCJ concurrent with any other sentence currently being served - Huber, GT, 1 days CFTS - Sentence to commence forthwith, $1694 fine inclusive of costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, $42.50 blood draw cost w/ 60 DTP or PP, 24 mo DL rev/IID, OWI Assess, DNA Sample and Surcharge. The Court has no objection to the sentence being served in another jurisdiction. Bond previously posted to be applied.

15CM260: $375 forfeiture w/ 60 DTP or PP, $42.50 Blood Draw Cost w/ 60 DTP or PP. 

16CM4: 90 days WCJ - Huber, GT, No CFTS - Consecutive to any other sentence currently being served - I/S - 1 year probation - Conditions: AODA and follow through, defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician to include but not limited to nitrous oxide, costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, DNA Sample and Surcharge.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.
